Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped) into ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @tomato{1%medium}(cut into 1cm chunks). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{5}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Remove the ends from the @green beans{some} and chop into thirds.

Put the @British chicken thighs{3} on a foil-lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle on some @oil{some}, grate over the @lemon{1/2}(zested) and sprinkle on the @dried oregano{1}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Squeeze over some @lemon juice{some} and rub in the flavours.

> Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Leave to one side. Put a large #saucepan{} of @water{750%ml}(for the risotto) on to boil. Add the @chicken stock powder{1} and stir to dissolve. Once boiling, turn the heat to low.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{some} in another large saucepan on medium heat and add the onion. Stir and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}, then add the garlic and the @tomato puree{15%g}. Mix well and cook for ~{1%minute} more, then add the @Arborio rice{175%g} and stir to coat in the garlicky oil. Add the @white wine vinegar{1/2} and allow it to evaporate.

Bake the chicken on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Halfway through
> cooking, sprinkle half of the hard Italian cheese over the chicken and pop
> back in the oven. Once cooked through, remove from the oven and cover with
> foil while you finish the risotto.

Sprinkle @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} over the chicken and pop back in
the oven.

In the meantime, add the tomato chunks and a ladle of stock to the rice. Stir
continually until the stock has been absorbed by the rice. Continue this
process until the rice is cooked, around ~{20-25%minutes}. Add the green beans
to the pan for the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking.

> Taste your rice, add a splash more water and cook for a few more mins if it is
> still a bit firm.

Once the rice is ready, stir through the remaining hard Italian cheese and a
squeeze of lemon juice. Stir in some @?butter{some} if you have some. Finish with
half the parsley and season with salt, pepper and lemon juice to taste. Cut
each chicken thigh into six slices. Spoon the risotto into #bowls{}, lay the
chicken on top and sprinkle over the remaining parsley. Enjoy!